\begin_layout Paragraph*

\emph on
Peng-Robinson Equation of State
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Peng-Robinson equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "PengDing-Yu_i160057a011"

\end_inset

 is an cubic Equation of State (characteristic related to the exponent of
 the molar volume) which relates temperature, pressure and molar volume
 of a pure component or a mixture of components at equilibrium.
 The cubic equations are, in fact, the simplest equations capable of representin
g the behavior of liquid and vapor phases simultaneously.
 The Peng-Robinson EOS is written in the following form
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
P=\frac{RT}{(V-b)}-\frac{a(T)}{V(V+b)+b(V-b)}\label{eq:PR}\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
where 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

