 as a function of temperature
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Equilibrium, where you must specify the equilibrium constant (K) as a function
 of temperature, a constant value or calculated from the Gibbs free energy
 of reaction (
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta G/R$
\end_inset

).
 The orders of reaction of the components are obtained from the stoichiometric
 coefficients.
\end_layout

