\begin_layout Subsection
Conversion Reaction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the conversion reaction it is assumed that the user has information regarding
 the conversion of one of the reactants as a function of temperature.
 By knowing the conversion and the stoichiometric coefficients, the quantities
 of the other components in the reaction can be calculated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Considering the following chemical reaction:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
aA+bB\rightarrow cC,\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

where 
\emph on
a
\emph default
, 
\emph on
b 
\emph default
and 
\emph on
c
\emph default
